docs.abstract: The consulting company has argued it’s too hard to understand the disclosure rules intended to keep bankruptcy proceedings honest. It could have just looked at “Bankruptcy 101.”

docs.lead_paragraph: McKinsey & Company has spent months fighting in court over how it should disclose potential conflicts of interest when it advises bankrupt companies. headline.main: McKinsey Said Disclosure Rules Were Confusing. It Ignored Its Own Primer.
